A 50-year-old man, Ahmadu Muhammad has been arraigned at a Kano Sharia Court, for allegedly intimidating a woman. Muhammad, who lives at Zaidawa Fulani Village in Danbatta, is facing a two-count charge of criminal use of force and intimidation. The Prosecutor, Insp. Abdul Wada, told the court that one Hajara Umaru of Zaidawa Fulani village, Danbatta, reported the matter at the Criminal Investigation Department (CID) Bompai Police Division, Kano on Dec. 20. He alleged that on the same day at about 07:00 p.m., the defendant had an argument with Umaru (the complainant) which led to Muhammad beating her with a cane and ordering his wives to kill her.   Police confirm attack on Sino-Hydro workers in Niger     DHQ warns politicians, others against use of military…     Lagos clears five Dowen students accused of killing…   - Advertisement - The prosecutor said the offence contravened Sections 266 397, 165 and 227 of the Penal Code. The defendant, however, pleaded not guilty to the charge. The Judge, Dr Bello Khalid, granted him bail with two reliable sureties. He said that the sureties must be his blood relations. Khalid adjourned the matter until Feb. 3 for mention. (NAN)